conclusion: Determine the time t1 for the lower end of the wooden rod to reach the upper end A of the cylinder.

Initial velocity v0 = 0 m/s, acceleration due to gravity g = 10 m/s^2, distance traveled s = 25 m.
Using the kinematic equation s = v0 t + (1/2) g t^2, substitute known values to get 25 = 5 t^2.
Solve for t: t^2 = 5, t = sqrt(5).
Calculate the final time t1: t1 = sqrt(5) â‰ˆ 2.24 seconds.
